Before the end of absolute monarchy, Swaziland was one of the only three really independent kingdoms in Africa along with neighbouring neighbouring nation of Lesotho and Togo.

From the 's onwards through Swaziland's history, the Swazi Kingdom has been gripped by political unrest. Swazis began to protest against the system itself and vociferously demanded a constitutional monarchy and more inclusive government.

This development came about after the death of king Sobhuza II, Modernity reached Swaziland through the influence of the YMCA and in the s and Swazi youths began to be attracted to western ideals of democracy, majority rule, individualism and socialism. The movement led to a few abortive insurrections in the s.
